messages.content: ComfyUI_StableCascadeLatentRatio is a custom node for creating empty latents for Stable Cascade, with purple background color, width and height incrementation of 64 by default, and more.
What are the default width and height increments for ComfyUI_StableCascadeLatentRatio?
The default width and height increments for ComfyUI_StableCascadeLatentRatio are both 64.
Is it possible to lock the aspect ratio in ComfyUI_StableCascadeLatentRatio?
Yes, it is possible to lock the aspect ratio in ComfyUI_StableCascadeLatentRatio.
How can I switch width and height in ComfyUI_StableCascadeLatentRatio?
To switch width and height in ComfyUI_StableCascadeLatentRatio, adjust the values at run time.
Where can I find the ComfyUI_StableCascadeLatentRatio node?
You can find the ComfyUI_StableCascadeLatentRatio node under the `latent/Stable Cascade Latent Ratio` category.

To install ComfyUI_StableCascadeLatentRatio, clone the repository into the `ComfyUI/custom_nodes` folder using the command 'git clone https://github.com/Guillaume-Fgt/ComfyUI_StableCascadeLatentRatio.git'.
Why are stage_c and stage_b batch sizes separated into two widgets in ComfyUI_StableCascadeLatentRatio?
Stage_c and stage_b batch sizes are separated into two widgets in ComfyUI_StableCascadeLatentRatio to enable the use of the Latent From Batch node.
